title: Optional Clause (ADR-196 C1)
story: friendly-zoo
description: The staff-gate status line's mid-sentence clause appears only while the gate is open — Optional present=false leaves no dangling punctuation (S9–S10, AC-13).
---

# Pick up the keycard at the entrance, then head to the gate.
> take keycard
[OK: contains "Taken"]

> south
[OK: contains "Main Path"]

# Gate CLOSED: the Optional clause is absent and the sentence ends cleanly.
> examine staff gate
[OK: contains "The staff gate is set into the fence."]
[OK: not contains "standing wide open"]

# Unlock and open the gate.
> unlock staff gate with keycard
[OK: contains "unlock"]

> open staff gate
[OK: contains "open"]

# Gate OPEN: the Optional clause now renders inline, before the period.
> examine staff gate
[OK: contains "The staff gate is set into the fence, standing wide open."]
